<title>FRANCE: Algeria, BHP sign US$62 mln deal.</title>
<headline>Algeria, BHP sign US$62 mln deal.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Algeria's oil state-run Sonatrach signed a US$62 million deal with Australia's Broken Hill Pty Co Ltd (BHP) on Saturday for oil and gas exploration and exploitation, Algeria's official APS news agency reported.</p>
<p>The agreement, signed in Algiers, covers exploration and exploitation in Boukhechba area, northwest of Illizi basin, for 10 years, APS said. Eight wells were expected to be drilled in Boukhechba area, it said.</p>
<p>APS said the $62 million agreement with BHP was the second of its kind concluded since Algeria liberalised its oil and gas laws in 1991 to attract foreign investors.</p>
